-- Wall Street regulator to consider mandating broker background checks
-- 
-- Wed Apr 16, 2014 12:46PM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, April 16 (Reuters) - Wall Street's self-funded regulator announced on Wednesday it will soon consider whether to propose new rules to require background checks for brokers.

The Financial Industry Regulatory Authority said in an online posting that its board will review the plan at an April 24 meeting. The announcement can be found here: http://www.finra.org/Industry/Regulation/Guidance/CommunicationstoFirms/P486188